From 79e3b49251a328adfeb19cddeffc1d7a012264fc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Keno Fischer <keno@alumni.harvard.edu>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 03:57:05 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] apple-codesign + app-store-connect: add AWS KMS signing
 backends

Adds an aws-kms Cargo feature to both crates:

* apple-codesign: new AwsKmsPrivateKey signing key backend. Signing
  operations call the KMS Sign API; the private key never leaves KMS.
  New CLI args: --aws-kms-key, --aws-kms-certificate-file,
  --aws-kms-region (and an [sign.aws_kms] config file section).
* app-store-connect: ConnectTokenEncoder gains an Es256Signer trait
  so ES256 JWTs can be minted by external signers. New
  AwsKmsEs256Signer implementation. UnifiedApiKey can reference an
  AWS KMS key (aws_kms_key/aws_kms_region) instead of embedding
  private key material, so the api key JSON file is no longer secret.
* rcodesign encode-app-store-connect-api-key gains --aws-kms-key /
  --aws-kms-region.

Credentials resolve via the standard AWS SDK provider chain, including
OIDC web identity federation (AWS_WEB_IDENTITY_TOKEN_FILE/AWS_ROLE_ARN),
enabling secretless code signing + notarization from CI.
